# DI (Koin) and Navigation

## Koin Modules

Each feature module contains its own Koin modules:

- `feature{Name}ImplModule` — Repository, ApiClient, StoreFactory, data mappers
- `feature{Name}PresentationModule` — ViewModel, UI mappers

Rules:
- Use `new(::Impl)` — Koin resolves dependencies automatically, no need to list parameters manually
- Import: `import org.koin.core.module.dsl.new` (**not** `org.koin.dsl.new`)
- `viewModelOf(::ViewModel)` for ViewModels
- Grouping: `factory` for Repository, ApiClient, Mapper; `factory` for StoreFactory

```kotlin
// impl/di/
internal val feature{Name}ImplModule = module {
    factory<{Feature}Repository> { new(::{Feature}RepositoryImpl) }
    factory<{Feature}ApiClient> { new(::{Feature}ApiClientImpl) }
    factory<ItemMapper> { new(::ItemMapperImpl) }
    factory { new(::{Feature}StoreFactory) }
}

// presentation/di/
internal val feature{Name}PresentationModule = module {
    factory<Ui{Feature}StateMapper> { new(::Ui{Feature}StateMapperImpl) }
    factory<Ui{Feature}LabelMapper> { new(::Ui{Feature}LabelMapperImpl) }
    viewModelOf(::{Feature}ViewModel)
}
```

## Navigation

Screens are defined in `core-navigation/Screen.kt`. `Screen` is a plain interface; routes are top-level `@Serializable data object`s:

```kotlin
interface Screen

@Serializable
data object {Feature}Route : Screen
```

Screen API in the `ui` module:

```kotlin
fun NavGraphBuilder.composable{Feature}Screen(
    onNavigateToNext: () -> Unit,
) {
    composable<{Feature}Route> {
        {Feature}Screen(onNavigateToNext = onNavigateToNext)
    }
}

fun NavController.navigateTo{Feature}Screen() {
    navigate({Feature}Route)
}
```

In NavHost:

```kotlin
NavHost(navController = navController, startDestination = {Feature}Route) {
    composable{Feature}Screen(onNavigateToNext = { navController.navigateTo{Next}Screen() })
}
```
